# {{obsolete form of|en|yolk}}
====Usage notes====
* Some 19th-century authorities regarded this as the correct spelling.
** '''1828''', [[w:Noah Webster|Noah Webster]], ''An American Dictionary of the English Language'', "[https://web.archive.org/web/20100609203426/http://machaut.uchicago.edu/?resource=Webster%27s yelk]":
**: It is sometimes written and pronounced yolk, but yelk is the proper word. Yolk is a corruption.
